00:03:03.910 --> 00:03:05.451
The common man,
common woman in India

00:03:05.451 --> 00:03:07.770
and the connection you
have all over the country.

00:03:07.770 --> 00:03:09.397
So can you talk a
little bit about it?

00:03:09.397 --> 00:03:11.730
SHAH RUKH KHAN: I never wanted
to be an actor, actually.

00:03:11.730 --> 00:03:14.820
I was wanting to be either
a software engineer,

00:03:14.820 --> 00:03:20.600
or-- No, really.

00:03:20.600 --> 00:03:23.020
At that time, it was very new.

00:03:23.020 --> 00:03:26.320
It wasn't as easily
spoken as now,

00:03:26.320 --> 00:03:29.810
and so I did give my
entrance exam in the IT.

00:03:32.640 --> 00:03:35.810
It seems like a joke, but I did.

00:03:35.810 --> 00:03:36.490
I look stupid.

00:03:36.490 --> 00:03:36.990
I'm not.

00:03:36.990 --> 00:03:38.365
I'm really
intelligent, you know?

00:03:38.365 --> 00:03:40.630
And just to let you
know, I did electronics.

00:03:40.630 --> 00:03:42.645
I got 98, which is the
highest in India ever.

00:03:45.340 --> 00:03:47.451
Those were the days
of diodes and triodes.

00:03:47.451 --> 00:03:48.950
It wasn't with the
chips and things.

00:03:48.950 --> 00:03:51.370
SUNDAR PICHAI: Anytime you want
to switch careers, let me know.

00:03:51.370 --> 00:03:51.530
SHAH RUKH KHAN: I'd love to.

00:03:51.530 --> 00:03:52.680
Yeah.

00:03:52.680 --> 00:03:55.760
And then, I wanted
to be in sports.

00:03:55.760 --> 00:03:58.860
I didn't want to act,
in film especially.

00:03:58.860 --> 00:04:00.990
I kind of-- not
looked down upon it,

00:04:00.990 --> 00:04:03.620
but never thought I'm cut
out for Indian cinema.

00:04:03.620 --> 00:04:06.370
I did a bit of English theatre
with Mr. Barry John in Delhi.

00:04:06.370 --> 00:04:07.170
I'm from Dehli.

00:04:07.170 --> 00:04:15.040
And then, I hurt
myself-- my lower back.

00:04:15.040 --> 00:04:16.529
And one thing led to the other.

00:04:16.529 --> 00:04:18.734
There was a play
being done and I

00:04:18.734 --> 00:04:21.670
know the people, all the
girls from Delhi Lady Shri Ram

00:04:21.670 --> 00:04:23.890
College.

00:04:23.890 --> 00:04:27.670
So there's a girls' college,
and they needed seven boys

00:04:27.670 --> 00:04:29.550
to act with 85 girls.

00:04:29.550 --> 00:04:35.970
And I got a job as a principal
dancer, not as an actor.

00:04:35.970 --> 00:04:38.820
I had one line-- Annie Get
Your Gun, it's a famous play--

00:04:38.820 --> 00:04:41.690
and I got a line in it,
which I said, "Annie, I

00:04:41.690 --> 00:04:44.200
have a letter for you."

00:04:44.200 --> 00:04:45.640
And it started like that.

00:04:45.640 --> 00:04:47.470
And I continued with theatre.

00:04:47.470 --> 00:04:50.010
Television became big in India.

00:04:50.010 --> 00:04:52.670
Yeah, television started.

00:04:52.670 --> 00:04:54.799
I went to get a house on rent.

00:04:54.799 --> 00:04:56.340
Instead, I got a
rolling [INAUDIBLE].

00:04:58.841 --> 00:05:01.090
Some years later, a year
later, it became very popular

00:05:01.090 --> 00:05:02.100
and I got a phone call.

00:05:05.250 --> 00:05:09.450
Somebody said, I'm [INAUDIBLE].

00:05:09.450 --> 00:05:11.860
I'm like no, this has
to be somebody else.

00:05:11.860 --> 00:05:12.850
It's not a real call.

00:05:12.850 --> 00:05:14.600
And they said, would
you like to do films?

00:05:14.600 --> 00:05:15.890
And I said, no.

00:05:15.890 --> 00:05:17.175
I'm not interested in films.

00:05:17.175 --> 00:05:18.550
And then, something
sad happened.

00:05:18.550 --> 00:05:19.570
My parents expired.

00:05:19.570 --> 00:05:20.195
And I said, OK.

00:05:20.195 --> 00:05:21.195
I want to stay in Delhi.

00:05:21.195 --> 00:05:22.060
I was feeling sad.

00:05:22.060 --> 00:05:24.374
So I went over to
Mumbai for a year.

00:05:24.374 --> 00:05:26.040
I told my friends,
I'm back in one year.

00:05:26.040 --> 00:05:28.230
I'm going to do five films,
get over the sadness.

00:05:28.230 --> 00:05:29.460
And it's been 25 years.

00:05:29.460 --> 00:05:30.751
I'm still not going back today.

00:05:30.751 --> 00:05:31.930
I'm still here.

00:05:31.930 --> 00:05:35.609
So my growth has been of someone
who has not really thought out

00:05:35.609 --> 00:05:36.650
that I would be an actor.

00:05:36.650 --> 00:05:37.358
It just happened.

00:05:37.358 --> 00:05:38.700
One thing led to the other.

00:05:38.700 --> 00:05:41.962
And I don't know if I'm
a good actor or not.

00:05:41.962 --> 00:05:43.420
If I act well, if
I do well or not.

00:05:43.420 --> 00:05:49.522
But I don't ever describe
the process too seriously.

00:05:49.522 --> 00:05:50.980
I think it's very
boring for people

00:05:50.980 --> 00:05:52.910
to hear how the art works.

00:05:52.910 --> 00:05:57.010
I truly believe the art is much
more important than the artist.

00:05:57.010 --> 00:05:59.620
And I'm very humble about
the fact there are so

00:05:59.620 --> 00:06:01.940
many people like me, and
I'm very, very grateful.

00:06:01.940 --> 00:06:03.620
So what I do is I
take things from life

00:06:03.620 --> 00:06:06.410
and just continue acting,
have fun, smile a lot,

00:06:06.410 --> 00:06:07.180
and share a lot.

00:06:07.180 --> 00:06:08.680
I think acting is about giving.

00:06:08.680 --> 00:06:10.970
I think somehow that's
made people like me

00:06:10.970 --> 00:06:13.608
a little more than
the talent I have.

00:06:13.608 --> 00:06:17.420
[APPLAUSE]

