ABHISHEK BACHCHAN: Is
it just San Francisco?

00:14:28.360 --> 00:14:32.190
Why are all the guys
only asking for me?

00:14:32.190 --> 00:14:34.117
Even last night, remember?

00:14:34.117 --> 00:14:34.992
SHAH RUKH KHAN: Yeah.

00:14:40.187 --> 00:14:42.270
SUNDAR PICHAI: I was hoping
my name would come up.

00:14:44.501 --> 00:14:46.084
ABHISHEK BACHCHAN:
(SCREAMING) Sundar!

00:14:54.890 --> 00:14:56.570
SUNDAR PICHAI: So they're here.

00:14:56.570 --> 00:14:58.570
They're also doing
show-promoting the new movie.

00:14:58.570 --> 00:15:00.390
It's called, "Happy New Year."

00:15:00.390 --> 00:15:02.066
It's premiering for Diwali.

00:15:02.066 --> 00:15:03.690
So maybe you guys
can talk a little bit

00:15:03.690 --> 00:15:05.398
about the movie, what
the movie is about,

00:15:05.398 --> 00:15:07.897
why you're excited
to be part of it?

00:15:07.897 --> 00:15:09.480
SHAH RUKH KHAN: Let
me first introduce

00:15:09.480 --> 00:15:12.490
Abhishek, who I've
known since childhood.

00:15:12.490 --> 00:15:16.660
He's a wonderful, wonderful
co-actor, friend and one

00:15:16.660 --> 00:15:22.690
of the most deranged and
fun person on the set.

00:15:22.690 --> 00:15:24.470
Most distracted,
but most lively.

00:15:24.470 --> 00:15:27.640
And the happiest, happiest
person that I work with.

00:15:27.640 --> 00:15:29.119
So I thank him.

00:15:33.750 --> 00:15:36.060
Deepika, as you all know,
started with [INAUDIBLE].

00:15:38.960 --> 00:15:41.440
I like to show off and be
pompous and take the credit

00:15:41.440 --> 00:15:47.380
for the fact that I made
her, which I can say openly.

00:15:47.380 --> 00:15:49.930
And today,
unfortunately, she won't

00:15:49.930 --> 00:15:52.810
be able to sing because
her voice is gone.

00:15:52.810 --> 00:15:54.310
Otherwise, she would
have, normally.

00:15:54.310 --> 00:15:56.726
She does a full [INAUDIBLE]
as soon as she comes, when she

00:15:56.726 --> 00:15:57.610
[INAUDIBLE].

00:15:57.610 --> 00:15:59.240
She does a whole [INAUDIBLE].

00:15:59.240 --> 00:16:01.310
But she wouldn't
be able to do it.

00:16:01.310 --> 00:16:08.210
The film is a heist film mixed
with a dance competition.

00:16:08.210 --> 00:16:10.827
And easier to describe
it, though the stories

00:16:10.827 --> 00:16:12.660
are not copied, though
people will say that.

00:16:12.660 --> 00:16:15.900
But it's "Ocean's Eleven"
meets "Full Monty,"

00:16:15.900 --> 00:16:18.580
if that combination
can ever, ever happen.

00:16:18.580 --> 00:16:20.530
But Farah Khan
thought of the film

00:16:20.530 --> 00:16:22.430
where, like a
regular heist film,

00:16:22.430 --> 00:16:26.920
you have one guy-- a mastermind,
so to say-- who collects people

00:16:26.920 --> 00:16:30.470
with different specialities.

00:16:30.470 --> 00:16:32.290
Someone is a lock breaker.

00:16:32.290 --> 00:16:35.900
Somebody's-- obviously, there's
one-- is it OK to say "nerd"

00:16:35.900 --> 00:16:36.732
here?

00:16:36.732 --> 00:16:38.700
SUNDAR PICHAI: Yeah.

00:16:38.700 --> 00:16:42.380
I'm not one, but they all are.

00:16:42.380 --> 00:16:45.120
SHAH RUKH KHAN:
Or I'll be pelted.

00:16:45.120 --> 00:16:46.910
You have one
highly-sophisticated,

00:16:46.910 --> 00:16:48.900
intelligent computer hacker.

00:16:51.470 --> 00:16:54.700
And so on and so forth.

00:16:54.700 --> 00:16:57.330
Abhishek has a
speciality which really,

00:16:57.330 --> 00:17:00.960
really cannot be described,
because it's gross.

00:17:03.202 --> 00:17:05.410
But you'll get to see it
when you see it in the film.

00:17:05.410 --> 00:17:07.849
It's gross, the ability
that he has in the film.

00:17:07.849 --> 00:17:08.740
ABHISHEK BACHCHAN:
Special power.

00:17:08.740 --> 00:17:10.698
SHAH RUKH KHAN: The
special powers that he has.

00:17:10.698 --> 00:17:14.260
And I'll now defer-- I'll
request Deepika and Abhishek

00:17:14.260 --> 00:17:16.480
to tell you a little
more about what they do.

00:17:16.480 --> 00:17:22.229
Deepika, as you will hear now,
normally also sounds like this.

00:17:22.229 --> 00:17:24.770
DEEPIKA PADUKONE: I didn't think
I had that effect on people.

00:17:30.085 --> 00:17:31.210
ABHISHEK BACHCHAN: It's OK.

00:17:31.210 --> 00:17:33.456
It was an Apple.

00:17:33.456 --> 00:17:35.866
[LAUGHING]

00:17:42.892 --> 00:17:44.350
DEEPIKA PADUKONE:
I'm really sorry.

00:17:44.350 --> 00:17:47.130
I can't say much today
because I've lost my voice.

00:17:47.130 --> 00:17:50.175
SUNDAR PICHAI: I think people
are just happy looking at you.

00:17:50.175 --> 00:17:52.050
SHAH RUKH KHAN: We'll
do it in dumb charades.

00:17:52.050 --> 00:17:54.790
We'll do it like-- three words.

00:17:54.790 --> 00:18:00.850
Say, "How are you?"

00:18:00.850 --> 00:18:02.590
How-- second word?

00:18:06.090 --> 00:18:07.090
You.

00:18:07.090 --> 00:18:07.960
You.

00:18:07.960 --> 00:18:09.066
How are you?

00:18:09.066 --> 00:18:09.566
OK.

00:18:11.587 --> 00:18:13.087
SUNDAR PICHAI:
Abhishek, do you want

00:18:13.087 --> 00:18:14.720
to say a few words
about the movie?

00:18:14.720 --> 00:18:16.970
ABHISHEK BACHCHAN: Know that
it's an absolute pleasure

00:18:16.970 --> 00:18:19.644
to be here.

00:18:19.644 --> 00:18:21.060
Contrary to what
everybody thinks,

00:18:21.060 --> 00:18:23.290
we actually haven't
slept all night

00:18:23.290 --> 00:18:25.610
because we've all been
so excited to come here.

00:18:28.520 --> 00:18:31.430
Yeah.

00:18:31.430 --> 00:18:35.020
But very honestly, just
to see all the Desis out

00:18:35.020 --> 00:18:35.770
there is way cool.

00:18:39.750 --> 00:18:43.554
I mean, I don't mean to sound
too much of a nationalist,

00:18:43.554 --> 00:18:45.970
but it's just fantastic to see
that you guys are literally

00:18:45.970 --> 00:18:47.112
running the world, man.

00:18:51.906 --> 00:18:53.530
SUNDAR PICHAI: So we
do take questions,

00:18:53.530 --> 00:18:56.700
which people have all submitted
both internally and externally.

00:18:56.700 --> 00:19:00.270
And the most popular question
was throughout your career,

00:19:00.270 --> 00:19:03.000
who has been your inspiration
for each of you, and why?

00:19:03.000 --> 00:19:06.420
So if you could talk about that.

00:19:06.420 --> 00:19:07.460
ABHISHEK BACHCHAN: Me?

00:19:07.460 --> 00:19:08.376
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE].

00:19:11.180 --> 00:19:12.180
ABHISHEK BACHCHAN: Yeah.

00:19:12.180 --> 00:19:20.120
My eternal inspiration
has been-- so, yes.

00:19:20.120 --> 00:19:24.621
For me, it's always been
my father in whatever I do.

00:19:24.621 --> 00:19:25.120
Anything--

00:19:25.120 --> 00:19:25.930
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE].

00:19:25.930 --> 00:19:26.930
ABHISHEK BACHCHAN: Yeah.

00:19:26.930 --> 00:19:28.920
I love him, too.

00:19:28.920 --> 00:19:33.450
And he's actually very
jealous that I'm here today.

00:19:33.450 --> 00:19:37.690
He's more of a computer
geek than even me, so.

00:19:37.690 --> 00:19:42.820
Actually, he must be blogging
right now as we speak.

00:19:42.820 --> 00:19:43.320
So yes.

00:19:43.320 --> 00:19:44.445
It's always been my father.

00:19:44.445 --> 00:19:48.120
I think for not just his
professionalism, but just

00:19:48.120 --> 00:19:50.340
the kind of human
being that he is.

00:19:50.340 --> 00:19:52.450
His sense of morals and values.

00:19:52.450 --> 00:19:55.410
Things that I've always admired,
and I aspire to be like him.

00:19:55.410 --> 00:19:58.920
And whatever I do in life
is always for my parents.

00:19:58.920 --> 00:20:03.590
And so I think my parents have
been my inspiration always.

00:20:08.762 --> 00:20:09.720
DEEPIKA PADUKONE: Pass.

00:20:09.720 --> 00:20:11.190
SUNDAR PICHAI: Pass.

00:20:11.190 --> 00:20:12.690
SHAH RUKH KHAN: I
think even her dad

00:20:12.690 --> 00:20:14.230
must be an inspiration for her.

00:20:14.230 --> 00:20:16.870
Mr. Prakash Padukone, one of
the greatest, greatest sportsmen

00:20:16.870 --> 00:20:18.295
the country's ever produced.

00:20:18.295 --> 00:20:20.295
DEEPIKA PADUKONE: My
parents are my inspiration.

00:20:20.295 --> 00:20:21.620
SUNDAR PICHAI: There you go.

00:20:21.620 --> 00:20:25.030
SHAH RUKH KHAN: And who
is your speech coach?

00:20:25.030 --> 00:20:26.820
DEEPIKA PADUKONE: You.

00:20:26.820 --> 00:20:28.679
Since I started off with you.

00:20:28.679 --> 00:20:31.137
SHAH RUKH KHAN: (MOCKINGLY,
WITH HOARSE VOICE) Oh yo yo yo.

00:20:32.055 --> 00:20:33.180
Well, that's very sporting.

00:20:33.180 --> 00:20:34.490
DEEPIKA PADUKONE: You
walked into that one.

00:20:34.490 --> 00:20:35.365
SHAH RUKH KHAN: Yeah.

00:20:35.365 --> 00:20:37.932
This was very good.

00:20:37.932 --> 00:20:39.390
Can you do an
[INAUDIBLE] take-off?

00:20:42.168 --> 00:20:44.490
DEEPIKA PADUKONE:
I-- Gee, sorry.

00:20:49.200 --> 00:20:52.000
SHAH RUKH KHAN: I get inspired
by-- I've always said this,

00:20:52.000 --> 00:20:53.610
and it may sound
a little strange,

00:20:53.610 --> 00:20:55.970
but I get inspired
not by special people.

00:20:55.970 --> 00:20:57.690
I get inspired by
ordinary people.

00:20:57.690 --> 00:21:00.780
I find it's not special
to be a special.

00:21:00.780 --> 00:21:02.220
It's very special
to be ordinary.

00:21:02.220 --> 00:21:05.040
And I see people
who achieve so much

00:21:05.040 --> 00:21:07.880
with such little
facilities at hand.

00:21:07.880 --> 00:21:09.520
I get very inspired by that.

00:21:09.520 --> 00:21:13.650
In terms of big people-- of
course, my parents died early,

00:21:13.650 --> 00:21:15.380
but they were very
good teachers.

00:21:15.380 --> 00:21:17.060
So some of the
people I've liked may

00:21:17.060 --> 00:21:18.700
sound a little odd,
but Muhammad Ali.

00:21:18.700 --> 00:21:20.290
I like the boxer.

00:21:20.290 --> 00:21:22.330
I really get inspired
by his story.

00:21:22.330 --> 00:21:24.760
I get inspired by the
story of Mother Theresa.

00:21:24.760 --> 00:21:26.670
And I've never had
the opportunity

00:21:26.670 --> 00:21:29.540
to meet either of them, but
whatever little I've read.

00:21:29.540 --> 00:21:31.596
And I make it a point
to read about them,

00:21:31.596 --> 00:21:32.970
and that's why
maybe sometimes, I

00:21:32.970 --> 00:21:34.280
come across a little arrogant.

00:21:34.280 --> 00:21:36.113
Because of Muhammad
Ali, not Mother Theresa.

00:21:38.680 --> 00:21:41.750
But I like the way
he has led his life.

00:21:41.750 --> 00:21:43.880
But more than that, I
think I just get inspired.

00:21:43.880 --> 00:21:46.770
I find when I meet
people, I ask them--

00:21:46.770 --> 00:21:48.320
how do you come
here for the shoot?

00:21:48.320 --> 00:21:49.820
And they say, we
wake up at 5:00 AM.

00:21:49.820 --> 00:21:51.010
We take a local train.

00:21:51.010 --> 00:21:51.760
We've cooked food.

00:21:51.760 --> 00:21:53.310
We've brought the
kids to school.

00:21:53.310 --> 00:21:54.851
And now, we made it
here at 8 o'clock

00:21:54.851 --> 00:21:56.360
and when we pack
up at 8:00, chances

00:21:56.360 --> 00:21:59.040
are we don't make it back home
until 4:00 AM again, sometimes.

00:21:59.040 --> 00:22:01.140
And I get really inspired
by ordinary people.

00:22:01.140 --> 00:22:02.680
And that inspiration,
I take that.

00:22:02.680 --> 00:22:06.620
I've gotten unfortunate now,
and I'm no longer ordinary.

00:22:06.620 --> 00:22:09.271
And I should retain that
ordinariness around me

00:22:09.271 --> 00:22:10.770
to be able to achieve
a little more.

00:22:14.747 --> 00:22:16.580
SUNDAR PICHAI: Another
question which people

00:22:16.580 --> 00:22:17.880
ask is about YouTube.

00:22:17.880 --> 00:22:20.850
So how does the Bollywood
industry look at YouTube?

00:22:20.850 --> 00:22:24.337
It's very popular in India.

00:22:24.337 --> 00:22:25.670
What do you think about YouTube?

00:22:25.670 --> 00:22:27.961
And there are many people
who work on YouTube here, so.

00:22:31.270 --> 00:22:34.558
ABHISHEK BACHCHAN:
Deepika will speak.

00:22:34.558 --> 00:22:36.266
DEEPIKA PADUKONE: I'm
feeling so useless.

00:22:36.266 --> 00:22:37.182
SUNDAR PICHAI: I know.

00:22:37.182 --> 00:22:39.162
DEEPIKA PADUKONE: So sorry.

00:22:39.162 --> 00:22:40.158
AUDIENCE: Keep smiling.

00:22:44.525 --> 00:22:46.400
SHAH RUKH KHAN: I think
it's very, very cool.

00:22:46.400 --> 00:22:49.630
I think it's really fantastic.

00:22:49.630 --> 00:22:52.790
I get a little frazzled when I
have to put that over-18 thing.

00:22:52.790 --> 00:22:54.500
That is a little confusing.

00:22:54.500 --> 00:22:57.700
They have their little-- that
word that you have to type

00:22:57.700 --> 00:22:58.500
what you can see.

00:22:58.500 --> 00:23:00.500
With my eyesight, it's
really, really difficult.

00:23:00.500 --> 00:23:04.100
It takes me five times to
tell them I'm 18 years old.

00:23:04.100 --> 00:23:06.650
Please, next time if you find
me putting in those numbers.

00:23:06.650 --> 00:23:07.610
No, I'm more than 18.

00:23:07.610 --> 00:23:10.940
Allow me to watch everything
on YouTube, please.

00:23:13.640 --> 00:23:14.490
I'm a busy actor.

00:23:14.490 --> 00:23:17.040
I don't get to pick out the
films I really want to watch,

00:23:17.040 --> 00:23:19.090
so I have to watch
them on YouTube.

00:23:19.090 --> 00:23:21.200
But I think it's
really, really nice.

00:23:21.200 --> 00:23:24.590
I spend my most fun
nights, actually,

00:23:24.590 --> 00:23:26.360
when my kids are back home.

00:23:26.360 --> 00:23:27.480
They're both grown up now.

00:23:27.480 --> 00:23:28.530
They're 16 and 14.

00:23:28.530 --> 00:23:31.320
My daughter and the little
one is still 16-17 months.

00:23:31.320 --> 00:23:34.130
But our biggest source
of entertainment

00:23:34.130 --> 00:23:35.320
is actually YouTube.

00:23:35.320 --> 00:23:37.660
